 to Weber's famous "Protestant ethic"—privileged the marvelous over the mundane, consumption over production, and the pleasures of enjoyment over the rigors of delayed gratification. By viewing money, luxury, and debt through the lens of sacramental theory, Coleman demonstrates that the modern economy casts far beyond rational action and disenchanted designs, and in ways that we have yet to apprehend fully.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCapitalismxReligious aspectsxCatholic Church. 0aCapitalismzFrancexHistoryy18th century. 0aEconomicsxReligious aspectsxCatholic Church. 7aHISTORY / Europe / France.2bisacsh  aCatholic Ethic.  aCommodity fetishism.  aDebt.  aEconomic theology.  aEighteenth Century.  aEnlightenment.  aLuxury.  aMoney.  apolitical economy.  athe Eucharist.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishz978311075408708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021z9783110753851oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073914540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361483340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503614833423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503614833/original  a978-3-11-073914-5  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075408-7  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2021  aZDB-23-DGGb2021